During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Kayleigh McEnany discussed President Trump's stance on racial and income disparities in America's education system. She highlighted the importance of school choice and the need for schools to reopen this fall. McEnany also presented data showing the negative impacts of sustained school closures on students' learning and well-being. She addressed questions about the Supreme Court rulings on Trump's taxes and DACA, as well as the CDC's guidelines for reopening schools. McEnany expressed the administration's support for hydroxychloroquine as a potential treatment for COVID-19 and emphasized the need for peace in the streets amidst recent violence.